Title: The Alderman
Type: Character
Source: V4

===

~ An expansionist ruler who genuinely believes the prophecy and genuinely believes the Order is hiding its fulfilment. This makes him more dangerous than a cynic.

He is not running a con. He is a man collecting what he believes the world promised him.

To him the logic is clean: whoever holds the Chosen One holds the continent. Not through tyranny — through the one power no army can resist. He has convinced himself this is not conquest. It is the peace the prophecy promised, delivered by the only man willing to reach for it.

When the Chosen One did not appear, his conclusion was rational given his premise: the Order is hiding her. His persecution of the Order is not, in his mind, cruelty. It is the collection of a debt.

He hunts Order members for two purposes he keeps separate in his mind: to eliminate anyone who knows the prophecy is a fraud, and to pressure those who might know where the Chosen One is. Both purposes are served by the same fire.

His scene with Fleur before the coronation — two people whose delusions find each other, neither knowing the other's full truth — should be one of the story's most uncomfortable scenes.
